But he returned to the United States and later declared himself innocent. A Mexican judge issued a warrant for his arrest and he was extradited in early February 2012.

During a jailhouse interview with CBS's 48 Hours Mystery taped later that month, Beresford-Redman once again proclaimed his innocence.

‘I didn't kill my wife, I really didn't,’ he from behind bars. ‘I can't imagine how anyone who listened to everything said could possibly think I had anything to do with killing my wife.’

Beresford-Redman worked on 48 episodes of the competition reality show Survivor between February 2002 and May 2004, while he also helped produce hit MTV car series Pimp My Ride.

‘Am I a survivor or not?’ Mr Beresford-Redman told CBS. ‘I think very much remains to be seen.’ 

